a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.00110853-e4ad-4689-8775-919b87160c2d.prompt=Enter a value for valueName a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.03989803-5ef3-4ac5-a4d9-3e6f3fb88662.transition.description=We just changed the value of ${valueName} in the registry a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.09dfd6f2-c7d6-4274-9301-89df7e953916.prompt=Enter a value for valueName a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.0a955486-72e8-45cf-b723-ffc5973cbc69.prompt=Enter a value for host a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.0b740834-0ed0-482a-b22d-904da2a4bb62.prompt=Enter a value for key a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.11c99414-95f3-44bb-ba2a-ae45069fdcbc.description=
Deletes a registry key

Inputs\:
host - hostname or ip address
key - The key to create. For Example\: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\Browser
recursive - true or false, whether to recursively delete child keys.
username - user to connect to host as
password - password to connect to host as

Responses\:
success - registry key deleted
failure - something went wrong

Returns\:
The raw XML response. Note, the format of this changes depending on the type of the key.
a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.16fce734-0636-44a5-8376-74235380565b.prompt=Enter a value for key a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.176f4180-c9e1-423d-8742-3d8b1181a5d1.transition.description=created ${key} a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.1db446bb-2522-4aee-b705-698bc582ae70.prompt=Enter a value for key a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.2bb70098-3112-44ca-b8a4-611b9dd35392.description=
Enumerates subkeys that live under a specific registry key.

Inputs\:
host - hostname or ip address
key - The key to create. For Example\: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\Browser
username - user to connect to host as
password - password to connect to host as

Responses\:
success - registry key values were enumerated
failure - something went wrong

Returns\:
The raw XML response.

Extra Results\:
subKeys - a Comma delimited list of the keys that are children of this key.
a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.2bcf50f5-78b5-410e-ae1f-238519ed5214.prompt=Enter a value for host a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.30b1ca2b-fc5e-4380-854c-9cbea33ce681.transition.description=Now that we are done we have deleted out subkey a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.37d85dd1-ae9d-4d73-8dbb-c769b3e8e22d.prompt=Enter a value for valueName a0135f1d-2534-4489-83d5-b1129d2000b0.3a80c76d-f7d3-42ea-b45b-2a0b6404a3aa.description=
Reads a value from a registry key

Inputs\:
host - hostname or ip address
key - The key to read from. For Example\: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\Browser
valueName - the name of the value in the key to read.
username - user to connect to host as
password - password to connect to host as

Responses\:
success - value read
failure - something went wrong

Returns\:
The raw XML response. Note, the format of this changes depending on the type of the key.

Extra Results\:
type - The type of the registry key.
value - the value of the registry key. If the type is REG_BINARY or REG_MULTI_SZ it will return a newline delimited list containing the elements of the array stored in the registry.

NOTE\: Some environment variables may be filled in by the registry api when reading keys. Be careful when modifying.

This sample demonstrates how to manipulate the Windows Registry.

Inputs\:
host - the host to manipulate the registry on during the sample.
username - an administrator user on host.
password - password for username.
key - A test key that will be created and deleted.
valueName - The name of a value to create\delete
value - the first value that will be set to valueName (NOTE\: it is also changed to a surprise value).

Responses\:
success - all operations completed.
failure - something went wrong.
